        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): activate selected harness plugins",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nAfter a gateway restart, agent harness selection could run before the selected plugin was activated. That kept Copilot and correctly configured external harness plugins unavailable despite a valid manifest and configuration. The BTW side-question path had the same ordering gap.\n\n## Why This Is The Right Fix\n\nHarness activation now uses the shared manifest activation plan for the selected runtime. It preserves disabled-plugin and restrictive-allowlist policy, requires explicit trust for workspace manifest owners, retains Codex provider-owner compatibility, and skips registry work for built-in and CLI-alias runtimes. BTW prepares the selected harness before both initial and canonical-model selection.\n\n## User Impact\n\nConfigured Codex, Copilot, and trusted plugin-owned harnesses are available on a cold gateway after restart. Untrusted workspace manifests cannot activate themselves.\n\n## Release Note\n\nFixes cold-start routing for configured agent harness plugins.\n\n## Validation\n\n- node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/harness/runtime-plugin.test.ts src/agents/btw.test.ts src/plugins/activation-planner.test.ts (70 tests)\n- Blacksmith Testbox tbx_01kvpp3hr4zdqw796nsdmm1f31: corepack pnpm build\n- Blacksmith Testbox tbx_01kvpp3hr4zdqw796nsdmm1f31: corepack pnpm check:changed passed all changed-path guards; the remaining core tsgo failure is unchanged on main at src/agents/embedded-agent-runner/tool-result-context-guard.ts:11\n- autoreview --mode local --engine codex: clean",
